# Commands Cheat Sheet

## VM Lifecycle

```bash
vagrant suspend          # Suspend VMs (fast resume, saves RAM state to disk)
vagrant resume           # Resume from suspend
vagrant halt             # Shutdown VMs cleanly
vagrant up               # Start halted VMs
vagrant destroy -f       # Nuke VMs entirely — needs `vagrant up` to rebuild
vagrant status           # Check VM status
vagrant ssh k3s-master   # SSH into master
```

---

## Cluster Health

```bash
# All nodes
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl get nodes -o wide'

# All pods (all namespaces)
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl get pods -A'

# All LoadBalancer IPs
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl get svc -A --field-selector spec.type=LoadBalancer'
```

---

## Apps

```bash
# Deploy / redeploy apps
./deploy-all.sh

# Watch rollout
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl rollout status deployment/commitment-tracker-api'

# Tail API logs
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl logs -f -l app=commitment-tracker-api --tail=50'

# Headlamp token (paste into Headlamp UI)
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl get secret headlamp-token -n kube-system -o jsonpath="{.data.token}" | base64 -d && echo'
```

