## Troubleshooting

### Helm release stuck ("another operation in progress")

```bash
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'helm uninstall monitoring -n monitoring 2>/dev/null || true; \
  kubectl delete secret -n monitoring -l owner=helm,name=monitoring 2>/dev/null || true; \
  sleep 2; helm list -n monitoring -a'
# Then re-run ./deploy-monitoring.sh
```

### Grafana crash — duplicate default datasource

kube-prometheus-stack v82+ and loki-stack both set `isDefault: true` in their datasource ConfigMaps.
Grafana 12.x hard-fails on this. The fix is baked into `deploy-monitoring.sh`. If it recurs:

```bash
vagrant ssh k3s-master -c 'kubectl patch configmap loki-loki-stack -n monitoring --type merge \
  -p "{\"data\":{\"loki-stack-datasource.yaml\":\"apiVersion: 1\ndatasources:\n- name: Loki\n  type: loki\n  access: proxy\n  url: http://loki:3100\n  version: 1\n  isDefault: false\n  jsonData: {}\n\"}}"'
kubectl delete pod -n monitoring -l app.kubernetes.io/name=grafana
```
